excerpt: Art-rich Gothic-style Lutheran church, featuring the world's tallest steeple & a noted carved choir.
detail_description: The Ulmer Münster is a Lutheran church built in Gothic style, located in the heart of Ulm City. It boasts the world's tallest steeple at 161.53 meters high and features an impressive carved choir. The church is considered a must-visit landmark in Germany, offering visitors a glimpse into the Middle Ages with its lovely Gothic architecture.
name: Ulm Minster

detail_description: Kunsthalle Weishaupt, located in Ulm, Germany, is a modern art gallery founded in 1984 by the city of Ulm. The gallery is housed in a cube-shaped building designed by Wolfram Wohr and named after entrepreneur and art patron Siegfried Weishaupt.
name: Kunsthalle Weishaupt

detail_description: Museum in der Klostermühle - Museumsverein Ulm-Söflingen e. V. houses an impressive collection of Upper Swabian art and culture, showcasing remarkable pieces of art, archaeology, and history. Among its treasures is the 40,000-year-old Lion Man, a mammoth ivory carving recognized as the oldest known animal carving globally.
name: Museum in der Klostermühle - Museumsverein Ulm-Söflingen e. V.

excerpt: Landmark Renaissance-era town hall of Ulm, noted for its exterior frescoes & astronomical clock.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Ulm, the Ulmer Rathaus stands as a stunning testament to Renaissance architecture and local heritage. This remarkable town hall, which began construction in the 13th century, boasts an intricately frescoed facade that captivates visitors with its vibrant colors and historical significance. The murals tell stories of Ulm's past, making it feel like a living history book right before your eyes.
name: Ulmer Rathaus

detail_description: Fischerviertel-Blau, located in Ulm, Germany, is a picturesque area known for its association with the Blau River. The river originates from the karst spring in Blaubeuren and runs through the Fischerviertel quarter before joining the Danube. This charming neighborhood features small and large blue channels that are fed by the clear waters of the Blautopf spring in nearby Blaubeuren, creating a serene environment where trout can be spotted.
name: Fischerviertel Ulm

excerpt: Baroque Benedictine monastery, founded in 1093 & expanded in 1714, featuring a rococo library.
detail_description: Wiblingen Abbey is a Baroque Benedictine monastery with a rich history dating back to 1093. It was later repurposed as barracks before being restored to its former glory. The highlight of the abbey is the rococo library, which is described as breathtaking and well-maintained. Visitors are encouraged to explore the convent building and museum, particularly the stunning library with its impressive ceiling paintings.
name: Wiblingen Abbey

excerpt: Museum set over 3 floors exploring the art, history & craft of bread making, baking & milling.
detail_description: Museum Brot und Kunst - Forum Welternährung is a privately-run museum that spans across three floors, dedicated to exploring the art, history and craft of bread making, baking and milling. The exhibits provide an in-depth look at bread from various perspectives beyond its role as a source of nourishment. Visitors can enjoy interactive displays and an audio guide available in English, French or German with separate guides for children. Additionally, the museum runs workshops on these topics throughout the year.
name: Museum Brot und Kunst - Forum Welternährung

detail_description: Museum Ulm, established in 1924, is a captivating destination that offers a diverse range of art objects, utilitarian items, and historical artifacts spanning from the Ice Age to modern times. The museum's Archaeological Collection presents an extensive timeline from the Neanderthal era to the early modern period, featuring remarkable pieces such as the iconic Ice Age Lion Man sculpture.
name: Museum Ulm

detail_description: Located under the towering spire of Ulm Minster, Stadthaus is a modern addition to the city's skyline. Designed by New York architect Richard Meier and opened in 1993, this striking white building hosts a variety of events including conferences, lectures, concerts, and exhibitions spanning art to science. Visitors can also enjoy a nice cafe within the premises. The spacious interior often features captivating photography exhibitions and is known for its welcoming atmosphere.
name: Stadthaus Ulm

detail_description: Glacis Park is a delightful destination in the city, offering a serene escape from sightseeing. The park features picturesque walking paths, charming ducks and swans, and vibrant flowers that bloom beautifully in the spring. Families will appreciate the two playgrounds available for children to enjoy. Additionally, visitors can relax at the cafe or Biergarten during the warmer seasons.
name: Glacis Park

detail_description: The Ulm City Wall, also known as Ulmer Stadtmauer, is a historic site in Ulm, Germany, erected in the 15th century. It features iron rings pointing towards the Danube River and offers a pleasant walk with views of the city and the river. The area is rich in cultural events and provides a great vantage point to admire beautiful buildings and enjoy the scenery.
name: Ulm city wall

excerpt: Small zoo with a bear enclosure & reptile house, plus tropical birds, an aquarium & a petting area.
detail_description: Tiergarten Ulm is a zoo and aquarium in the city of Ulm, offering a diverse range of animals including bears, wallabies, snakes, turtles, and tropical birds. It's an ideal destination for families with kids or animal enthusiasts. The facility has a rich history dating back to 1935 and was reopened in 1966 after a temporary closure during World War II.
name: Tiergarten Ulm

detail_description: Located in the fishing district near the Danube, Schwörhaus is a captivating red and yellow baroque building from the 17th century. Today, it serves as the city museum. Every year, the elected mayor takes an oath here in front of residents. The building holds historical significance and houses an intriguing archive that tells the impressive story of Ulm. It's not only a great place to explore Ulm's history but also offers a glimpse into its oldest building.
name: Schwörhaus

detail_description: Fischkastenbrunnen is a historical fountain located directly behind the town hall. It is surrounded by taverns, cafes, and bistros where visitors can sit comfortably and enjoy the ambiance. The square at the town hall offers plenty of dining options, with occasional live music performances adding to the lively atmosphere. Despite a lack of information about its name origin, this beautiful fountain makes for a great photo opportunity and is definitely worth a visit while exploring the pedestrian zone.
name: Fischkastenbrunnen Ulm

excerpt: Ulm is a city in the south German state of Baden-Württemberg, founded in medieval times. In the center is the huge Gothic Ulm Minster, a centuries-old church. Its steeple has views of the city and, in clear weather, the Alps. The Town Hall has an early-Renaissance facade, murals and a 16th-century astronomical clock. Half-timbered houses line the narrow alleys of the Fischerviertel, an area close to the River Danube.
detail_description: Ulm, a city in the south German state of Baden-Württemberg, is steeped in medieval history and architectural marvels. The Gothic Ulm Minster, with its towering steeple offering panoramic views of the city and the Alps on clear days, stands at the center. The town hall boasts an early-Renaissance facade adorned with murals and houses a 16th-century astronomical clock.
name: Ulm

excerpt: Family water park offering slides & a sauna area, plus an ice rink.
name: Donaubad

excerpt: Neu-Ulm is the seat of the Neu-Ulm district and a town in Swabia, Bavaria. Neighbouring towns include Ulm, Senden, Pfaffenhofen an der Roth, Holzheim, Nersingen and Elchingen. The population is 58,978. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Neu-Ulm, located in the Swabia region of Bavaria, is a charming town with a population of nearly 59,000. Situated across the River Danube from the city of New Ulm, it offers picturesque views and a tranquil atmosphere. Surrounded by neighboring towns such as Ulm, Senden, and Elchingen, Neu-Ulm provides visitors with an opportunity to explore the rich cultural heritage and natural beauty of this Bavarian region.
name: Neu-Ulm

detail_description: The Grabenhäusle in Ulm, located on the northern edge of the old town, holds a rich history dating back to the Thirty Years' War when it served as accommodation for city soldiers. Over time, it has been completely renovated and transformed into one of the most popular sights in Ulm. The idyllic and historic surroundings make it a must-see destination.
name: Grabenhäusle Ulm

detail_description: Friedrichsau in Ulm is a vast and serene park that offers a peaceful escape from the hustle and bustle of city life. It's a favorite spot for both locals and tourists, providing ample opportunities for relaxation and recreation. The park features beautiful ponds, streams, and lush greenery, creating a picturesque setting for leisurely walks or simply unwinding amidst nature. Families can enjoy the large playground area while exploring the diverse plant life showcased with informative plaques.
name: Friedrichsau

excerpt: Vast collection of ancient to modern local & international art including works by Picasso & Klee.
detail_description: The 'Freunde des Ulmer Museums e.V.' is a treasure trove for art and history enthusiasts alike, showcasing an extensive collection that spans from ancient artifacts to contemporary masterpieces. Visitors can marvel at works by renowned artists such as Picasso and Klee, alongside medieval relics that highlight Ulm's rich historical significance. The museum offers a captivating journey through time, illustrating the evolution of human creativity and cultural heritage.
name: Freunde des Ulmer Museums e.V.

detail_description: Bundesfestung Ulm, Fort Unterer Kuhberg, Werk XXIX is a historic site that offers a variety of attractions. It is the second largest fort in the federal testing area and now serves as a venue for various activities. The Illerblick independent Waldorf school and other organizations are housed within its premises.
name: Bundesfestung Ulm, Fort Unterer Kuhberg, Werk XXIX

detail_description: Albert-Einstein-Linde is a city that embraces both irony and determination. It is the birthplace of the renowned physicist, and boasts attractions such as the planned Einstein Museum and the longstanding Einstein Fountain, where visitors can witness his playful side.
name: Albert-Einstein-Linde Ulm

detail_description: Ulmer Höhenweg, located just outside the city, offers a 20-kilometer signposted footpath with stunning views from various vantage points. The main 12-kilometer route includes attractions like the botanical garden and Wilhelmsburg, providing diverse breaks along the hike from Eselsberg to Bofingen or vice versa.
name: Ulmer Höhenweg, Eselsberg

detail_description: The Albrecht-Berblinger-Gemeinschaftsschule is located at the historic site where Albrecht Berblinger, a tailor renowned for inventing a flying machine, made his daring attempt to fly over the Danube in 1811. A bronze plaque commemorates this significant event, adding an air of adventure and innovation to the school's surroundings.
name: Albrecht-Berblinger-Gemeinschaftsschule

detail_description: Lesecafé Stadtbibliothek Ulm is a modern architectural marvel with its transparent glass design spanning four floors. It houses an extensive collection of books in various languages, including Ukrainian and Russian, and features a dedicated children's section as well as sheet music for musicians. Visitors can enjoy the picturesque city views, access free toilets, and peruse through numerous magazines. The library also boasts a cozy café serving delicious coffee and is staffed by friendly individuals.
name: Lesecafé Stadtbibliothek Ulm

detail_description: Ulmer Zelt is a popular festival in the city, held in May and June, offering a variety of music, theater, and dance performances. The event is organized by dedicated volunteers who create a special and intimate atmosphere for concert-goers. Visitors can enjoy a selection of food while being entertained by live music in a cozy setting. Despite the potential for long lines at the bar, attendees appreciate the attentive staff who provide free water during warm days.
name: ulmer zelt
go asia Supermarkt - Ulm
address: im UG Sedelhöfe, Albert-Einstein-Platz 3/1, 89073 Ulm, Germany

detail_description: Nestled near the historic Zeughaus, which boasts a rich history dating back to the early 14th century, the Kinderspielplatz am Zeughaus offers a delightful retreat for families. This charming children's playground is perfect for little ones to explore and play while surrounded by Ulm's fascinating heritage. The area combines historical significance with modern-day fun, making it an ideal spot for parents looking to enjoy some quality time with their kids in a picturesque setting.
name: Kinderspielplatz am Zeughaus

detail_description: The Altes Rathaus mit ehem. Schule is a stunning historical building that has been lovingly restored by the dedicated residents of Markbronn and Dietingen in recent years. This charming old town hall stands as a testament to community spirit, showcasing both beauty and character. It serves as a versatile venue for various celebrations, making it a cherished gem for locals looking to host special events in an enchanting setting.
name: Altes Rathaus mit ehem. Schule

detail_description: Nestled in the charming city of Ulm, the Metzgerturm, or Butcher's Tower, stands as a fascinating piece of history and architecture. This 36-meter tall rectangular tower leans at an angle of 3.3 degrees—less than its famous counterpart in Pisa but equally intriguing! The tower's origins date back to 1350 when it was built near a medieval slaughterhouse outside the city walls.
name: Metzgerturm

detail_description: The Albert Einstein Geburtshaus Denkmal is a monument located on the original site where Albert Einstein was born in Ulm. The house where he was born was destroyed during the war, and the monument now stands as a tribute to his legacy. It consists of 12 horizontal stones and 12 vertical stones, symbolizing the hours of day and night. While some visitors found it under construction, its significance remains profound.
name: Albert Einstein Geburtshaus Denkmal Ulm

excerpt: Brick tower built around 1349, part of the original city defenses & known for its slight lean.
detail_description: Nestled in the charming city of Ulm, the Metzgerturm, or Butchers Tower, stands as a remarkable piece of history dating back to 1340. This striking brick structure is part of the original medieval fortifications and boasts a unique lean of 2.05 meters, reminiscent of Italy's famous Tower of Pisa.
name: Metzgerturm

detail_description: Nestled along the banks of the Danube River, Rosengarten in Ulm is a hidden gem that offers a serene escape right in the heart of the city. Originally transformed from an unkempt area into this charming rose garden in 1970, it underwent further renovations in 2007 with contributions from local rose enthusiasts. Visitors are treated to an array of stunning roses, some exuding delightful fragrances that enhance the experience.
name: Rosengarten, Ulm

excerpt: Imposing stone fortress built in the 1840s, later a WWII refugee camp & postwar military base.
detail_description: Wilhelmsburg is a captivating destination that boasts an impressive stone fortress constructed in the 1840s. This historical site has served various purposes over the years, including a WWII refugee camp and a military base post-war. While the fortress itself may not offer much visually unless you explore its museum, the surrounding nature provides fantastic hiking opportunities.
name: Wilhelmsburg

excerpt: Sprawling botanical garden & arboretum with themed gardens, tropical plants & several greenhouses.
detail_description: The Botanical Garden of the University of Ulm is an expansive arboretum filled with diverse plant life and numerous themed gardens. With sprawling greenhouses and tropical flora, this garden offers visitors a chance to commune with nature in all its glory. Spanning 26 hectares, it boasts a variety of trees, flowers and plants including some exotic ones. While it's a pleasant place to take a walk, some visitors suggest that the garden could benefit from more attractions or activities.
name: Botanical Garden of the University of Ulm

detail_description: The Lion Fountain, although lacking seating options, was overall satisfactory. It exudes an exceptionally pleasant ambiance. This stunning water feature is a true masterpiece and serves as a visually appealing centerpiece. Its allure lies in its grandeur and captivating design. The absence of chairs or benches does not hinder one's enjoyment of the fountain's beauty.
name: Lion Fountain

detail_description: The Donauschwäbisches Zentralmuseum is a contemporary and visually appealing institution that showcases the history and culture of the Danube region and its inhabitants. Although not all areas are in the English language, there is an abundance of photographs and displays on offer. The museum provides an excellent opportunity to immerse oneself in the fascinating heritage of this area.
name: Donauschwäbisches Zentralmuseum

detail_description: The HfG-Archive, established by design pioneers Inge Scholl, Otl Aicher, and Max Bill in 1953, played a pivotal role in shaping modern design until its closure in 1968. This institution's legacy continues to influence designers and researchers alike. Visitors can explore the Ulm Museum's captivating exhibition that showcases the innovative teaching methods and iconic works from this remarkable period.
name: HfG-Archive

detail_description: The Tourist-Information Ulm / Neu Ulm is highly recommended for tourists as it provides an enjoyable and informative experience. Visitors can easily book guided city and Minster tours online, which are filled with fascinating historical facts. The professional and kind guides patiently answer all questions. Additionally, the staff, particularly Astrid, is friendly and helpful. The center also offers the Ulm Card, which is worth it for the bike rental alone.
name: Tourist-Information Ulm / Neu Ulm

detail_description: The Kasperle Theater, a beloved children's puppet theater, is sorely missed by its audience. Regular visits to the plays with grandchildren were always an enjoyable experience for all. The anticipation of the return of performances featuring characters like Kasperle and Schnuffi is high. This family-friendly theater is known for its engaging shows that involve active participation from children. With beautifully crafted productions that captivate young hearts, it's no wonder that many eagerly await the reopening of this delightful theater for kids.
name: Kasperle Theater

detail_description: The Theater Ulm is a versatile cultural venue that hosts a variety of performances including drama, ballet, music theater, and concerts. In addition to its regular program, the theater also showcases productions from the independent theater and music scene. The venue has received positive feedback for its great location and friendly staff. Visitors have enjoyed top-notch productions such as Cinderella and have praised the creativity and quality of performances.
name: Theater Ulm

detail_description: Donaustufen is a delightful spot that invites you to pause and soak in the rhythm of life around you. This public space offers a tranquil atmosphere perfect for unwinding, whether you're enjoying a moment of solitude or engaging in lively conversations with fellow visitors. With its viewing terrace, lush lawns, and comfortable benches, it’s an ideal place to admire stunning views of the city while watching the world go by.
name: Donaustufen

detail_description: The Erbiskasten Brunnen is a popular tourist destination known for its captivating charm. This enchanting attraction draws visitors from near and far due to its unique features. The Erbiskasten Brunnen is renowned for its mesmerizing allure, which captivates all who visit. Its irresistible appeal stems from various remarkable aspects that make it truly one-of-a-kind.
name: Erbiskasten Brunnen Ulm
